# Nestmile

## Design docs (required for UI work)

**Before** implementing or changing UI, layouts, or shared components:

1. Read [`docs/design-system-2026.md`](docs/design-system-2026.md) — **complete design system** (quiet luxury, affluent tier-1 audience).
2. Read [`docs/ui-design.md`](docs/ui-design.md) — shared components (`Select`, tokens, patterns).
3. Read [`docs/premium-redesign-plan.md`](docs/premium-redesign-plan.md) when changing nav, home, or premium surfaces.
4. Read the feature design doc when one exists (e.g. [`docs/shopping-ui-design.md`](docs/shopping-ui-design.md)).

**Skills (premium UI, imagery & brand):**

- [`.cursor/skills/premium-ui/SKILL.md`](.cursor/skills/premium-ui/SKILL.md) — quiet luxury, Fraunces, PageHero, nav order.
- [`.cursor/skills/image-curation/SKILL.md`](.cursor/skills/image-curation/SKILL.md) — hero images, AI prompts, legal sourcing.
- [`.cursor/skills/brand-assets/SKILL.md`](.cursor/skills/brand-assets/SKILL.md) — logo, favicon/app icons, palette, SEO/PWA.

**After** UI changes in the same session:

1. Update the relevant design doc(s) so they match the code.
2. Prefer shared components in `src/components/` — do not add one-off styled `<select>` elements.

